Legs rather robust, conspicuously setose, with numerous long erect setae (especially on tibiae); profemora nearly simple, with slight edge on inner side; protibiae enlarged at mid-length and with smooth, moderately projecting lobe in distal half (
Fig. 1
); penultimate tarsomere widened / flattened distally, with terminal tarsomere dorsally articulated in all tarsi.
